                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1598: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Nanking (<persName type="to">Peck</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 10, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. For the Minister. Your February 9, 4 p.m. Upon receipt by you of formal
                    proposal that payment of American portion of Boxer Indemnity be postponed,
                    please so inform Department and also forward your views with regard to the
                    proposal. Department would be interested also in your colleagues’ attitude
                    toward the proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
